column2: Pine pollen (yellow) on surface at shore line.  No algae.
Thunderstorms until 1: 30.  Water seems very clear- but shallower reading than 2 weeks prior.
Partly sunny- hazy.  More evidence of algae.
Bright with clouds- some algal bloom- but still excellent.
Bright sun- cloudless- pine pollen collecting in bays along shore.
Bright sun- pine pollen in bays.
Overcast- bright but looked like a storm coming- windy.
Algae bloom reduced secchi depth.  Sunny- partly cloudy.
Sunny- breezy (from south) - heavy algae accumulation in shore (north shore) .
Choppy but no whitecaps. partly cloudy- bright. but 50 degrees.
Sunny- ripples.  Seems to be less algae this year.
Sunny.  Algae more evident than at any time during the summer.  Calm.
Water blue-green and a little murky.  Sunny- strong southwest winds.  Water level on our chain has dropped 3.5 feet starting 9/28 and I need to get my boat into the boathouse.
Cloudy. vegetation 3-4 weeks ahead of normal. some green-brown algae.
Cloudy and bright. lake level rising. no concentration of algae.
South breeze 15-20 mph partly cloudy. chop.
Southwest breeze force 4 partly cloudy. chop
Cloudy and bright.  E breeze small waves.
N wind partly sunny. moderate waves.
Sunny- breezy (nw) - single loon. for 2nd straight year- vegetation 2-3 weeks ahead of "normal."
First pure sunny day since we arrived 6/14.
Windy- sunny.  Boat drifted off deep hole.
After a week of rain- beautiful- partly cloudy
Sunny- slight chop. Two ring-billed gulls followed an eagel to its roost. Hoping for crumbs
Lake levels on the chain are high for this date. Water is the clearest in memory. Pine pollen is here.
Partly sunny- 60's- wind came up during temp readings- blew me off the deep hole.
Used new integrated sampler and digital thermometer for first time.
Pine pollen and algae in early stages.
Sunny- breezy- wind blew me off Deep Hole.
Beautiful- indian summer- 65 F- calm- sunny.
70's clear- breezy with chop- a northwoods day!
70's partly cloudy- breezy- a few boats- loon calling
mostly sunny- soft breeze- 2-3 boats- quiet- perfect!!
flat calm- sunny- hot! mature eagle flying along SE shore- impressive as always
60's. Partly sunny- pleasant. Breeze. Satellite day- path 25.
70 degrees F. Partly sunny- slight breeze. Some spyrogyra.
68 degrees F.- Sunny- slight breeze. 3 mature eagles flying together. No spyrogyra.
